<br>
The standard sun revenants are pretty much cake. They proc a semi nasty disease DoT that does around 200 damage. But an earth pet with its innate resistance combined with an elemental shawl and a pair of daggers of symbols resists most of them. They drop up to 6pp and the occasional high end gem. The reavers are the higher level caster variety. They cast necro spells though they have no pets. With the recent upgrade they seem to like Chilling Embrace and Blood Boil. Get hit with both of these and you're in trouble. They have minimal hit points though. Two cast of Char and they're dead. Watch it though - they will gate. Actually almost all of the caster mobs here will gate. Either fight them on their spawn point or nuke hard once they drop to 40% health.<br>
<br>
Bloodtribes are also good experience. They come in standard warrior and shaman types. Can be found wandering in the desert and also in caves along the northern and southern zone walls. Easy to single pull inside the caves at 52. Seems like any of the static mobs can be a spawn point for a named. <br>
<br>
The aliens are on two different factions - tro jeg and everyone else. If you want to kill the aliens stay away from the tro jeg. They proc a fire spell that will tear a standard 51 earth pet to pieces in no time and they have lots of hit points. The other three alien races each have a specialty proc also - vas ren is a slow, grol baku is a stun and cral ligi is a root though as far as I can remember there aren't any cral ligi in SD. The vas ren wander around a lot but the grol baku are located mostly in a couple of static camps. These can be single pulled at 52 also. The grol baku especially can drop some nice stuff - got a pair of Follower's Sleeves which are a nice upgrade to gatorscale imo. Also some nice melee bracers.<br>
<br>
The animals and plants don't drop anything except rarely a high end gem. Very rare drops also include Cheetah Paw fetish and a prismatic feeler 1HS weapon from the lightcrawlers. If you're doing the TS quests a lot of the items for these drop in SD. Anything that will drop off the revenants or the vas ren will only come from static spawns - not the wanderers. <br>
<br>
At 54 or 55 I probably will go up on the plateau and hit the higher level revenants there. All in all this is one of the better zones I've seen since I hit 50. Very little competition and lots of spawns. Last night I got a yellow in around 3 hours in 53 which is pretty damn good experience any way you look at it. <br>
